        "text": "To stop the background agent and resume here:\n\n1. **Open the agents panel** — run `claude agents` in a new terminal, or press `Ctrl+\\` inside the Claude Code session where the agent is running.\n\n2. **Find the running agent** — it will be listed with its task description.\n\n3. **Stop it** — select it and press `s` (stop), or run `claude agents stop \u003ctask-id\u003e`.\n\n4. **Resume here** — once stopped, run `/resume` again in this session and it should load the prior context.\n\nAlternatively, if you don't need that session's state, you can just start fresh here — `/resume` without a prior stopped session will just begin a new conversation.",
